{"title_page": "P\u0131nar K\u00f6ksal", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name = Ay\u015fe P\u0131nar K\u00f6ksal\n| image = PinarKoksal.jpg\n| image_size = \n| caption = \n| birth_date = 1946\n| birth_place = [[Adana]], Turkey\n| death_date = {{death-date and age|19 August 2019|20 April 1946}}<ref name=sanattanyansimalar />\n| death_place = [[Ankara]], Turkey\n| other_names = \n| known_for =\n| occupation = Composer of Turkish classical music\n| nationality = Turkish\n}}\n'''Ay\u015fe P\u0131nar K\u00f6ksal''' (20 April 1946 \u2013 19 August 2019) was a Turkish composer of Turkish classical music.<ref name=\"sanart\" /> \nShe lived in [[Ankara]] at the time of her death.<ref name=sanattanyansimalar>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sanattanyansimalar.com/besteci-pinar-koksal-vefat-etti/4664/|title=Besteci P\u0131nar K\u00f6ksal vefat etti|date=20 August 2019|website=sanattanyansimalar.com|language=tr|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref><ref name=sozcu>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sozcu.com.tr/2019/gundem/ayse-pinar-koksal-vefat-etti-5291774/|title=Ay\u015fe P\u0131nar K\u00f6ksal vefat etti|website=www.sozcu.com.tr|language=tr|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref>'''<big>[https://www.pinarkoksal.com/ www.pinarkoksal.com]</big>'''\n\n== Life ==\nK\u00f6ksal was born in [[Adana]], and because her father was a civil servant her childhood was spent in different parts of [[Anatolia]]. She graduated from [[Kayseri]] High School and later studied [[pharmacy]], receiving her diploma from the Private Higher School of Pharmacy in Istanbul.\n\nShe worked for 13 years as a pharmacist, and she was deputy chair of the board at Pet Holding as well as chair of the board for the K\u00f6ksal Education Foundation. She was also a member of the Democratic Party Governing Board, and chair of the party's Art Committee.\n\nFrom 2001 to 2007 she was a member of the Ministry of Justice Penal Institutions and Detention Houses Monitoring Board, a post from which she resigned in April 2007 for reasons of health.\n\nShe was married to Prof. Dr. G\u00fcntekin K\u00f6ksal and had two daughters, Ay\u015fe and Zeynep, as well as five grandchildren: Kaya, Ege, Melissa, Rauf and Sinan.\n\nShe died on August 19, 2019, due to complications caused by an operation.<ref name=sanattanyansimalar /><ref name=sozcu />\n\n==Musical career==\nHer musical training began in [[Artvin]] at the age of 9 with [[mandolin]] and violin lessons<ref name=akustik /> from Hasan \u00c7\u0131tak (1955\u201357). At the age of 15 she took [[accordion]] lessons in Kayseri (1961\u201362), and at 36 piano lessons from Veli Gerasim. It was at this time that she made her first compositions (1982\u201383). Her very first composition was \"With You I'm Full, Without You an Empty Shell\" (Waltz of Happiness),<ref>{{YouTube|S46HpX5Ks40}}</ref> a work in the Acemk\u00fcrdi makam for which she wrote the words as well as the music. Her first lessons in Turkish Art Music came from the late composer and artist Sadi Ho\u015fses<ref name=sanart /> (1984). After 1996 she studied for an extended period from the tanburist and composer Y\u0131lmaz Pakal\u0131nlar.<ref name=sanart /> K\u00f6ksal played the lute<ref name=sanart /> and has composed some 120 works, of which 74 are in the TRT ([[Turkish Radio and Television Corporation]]) repertory.<ref name=sanart /> A number of her compositions have been arranged polyphonically, while her works are performed throughout Turkey by various choirs, as well as being rendered on radio stations and television channels. In the year 2000 her album \"\u0130\u00e7imdeki Duygular\" was released, comprising works performed by TRT and Ministry of Culture artists.\n\nHers were the first Turkish art music compositions to be performed polyphonically, on December 16, 2003, by the Orfeon Chamber Chorus with soprano Leyla \u00c7olako\u011flu, tenor Hakan Aysev and bass Deva \u00c7olako\u011flu under the direction of conductor Bujor Hoinic. Her works were sung in the musical fantasy ''Cabaret Opera'' staged by the State Opera and Ballet Company and directed by G\u00fcr\u00e7il \u00c7elikta\u015f, and this work became part of the opera repertory (2004\u20132005). Her works have also been performed by symphony orchestras.\n\nHer works are mentioned in three books by the composer [[Turhan Ta\u015fan]], ''Women Composers'' (2000),<ref name=womcom /> ''Pharmacist Artists in Turkish Music'' (2001) and ''Doctor and Pharmacist Artists in Turkish Music'' (2011). In his master's dissertation \"Steps Toward Modernization in Turkish Music During the Republican Era\" (2004) the kanun artist and composer Halil Alt\u0131nk\u00f6pr\u00fc gives composer K\u00f6ksal's works as examples. She has also served on the jury in the Turkish-Style Music Composition Contest held by TRT.<ref name=akustik />   Her compositions also appear in ''The Collected Works of Turkish Art Music Composers'' by Rahmi Kalayc\u0131o\u011flu. In addition, her instrumental works are part of ''Kanun Egzersizleri ve E\u011fitimi'' (Exercises and Training for the Kanun), a book by the kanun artist and composer \u00d6zdemir Haf\u0131zo\u011flu, who is on the faculty of the music department at the K.T.U. Fatih School of Education.\n\nK\u00f6ksal's album ''A\u015fk Senfonisi'' (Symphony of Love), featuring Hakan Aysev and G\u00f6ksel Baktagir, has been released in October 2010.\n\nIn terms of number of works in the TRT repertory she ranks in the top three among the 250 female composers since the 17th century.<ref name=sanart />\n\n==Other interests==\nIn addition to all these endeavors she was interested in psychology as well as all branches of art including cinema, painting, the theater and dance, and she was also a photographer. Her first solo exhibition of photography, \"Do\u011fan\u0131n \u00c7o\u015fkusu\", was held in February 2004,<ref name=akustik /> and her second, \"Do\u011fan\u0131n \u00c7o\u015fkusu II\", in May 2010. Both shows were held in [[Ankara]].\n\n==References==\n<references>\n<ref name=akustik>{{cite web|url=http://www.akustikmuzik.com/sanatcidetay.asp?id=25|title=PINAR K\u00d6KSAL|work=Akustik M\u00fczik|accessdate=2010-10-08}}</ref>\n<ref name=sanart>{{cite web|url=http://www.sanart.org.tr/PDFler/69.pdf|title=Women Composers in Turkish Classical (Allaturca) Music|work=International Congress of Aesthetics 2007 \"Aesthetics Bridging Cultures\"|author=Yasemin L\u00fcmal\u0131|date=2007-10-04|format=pdf|accessdate=2010-10-08}}</ref>\n{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Duygu-Pinari-Spring-Emotions-K\u00f6ksal/dp/B0038WCG4U|title=Duygu Pinari / Spring of Emotions|work=amazon.com|accessdate=2010-10-08}}\n<ref name=womcom>{{cite book|author=Turhan Ta\u015fan|title=Kadin Bestecileri (Women Composers)|publisher=Pan Yayincilik|year=2000|location=Istanbul}}</ref>\n</references>\n\n==Further reading==\n*Turhan Tasan, ''Kadin Bestecileri'' [Women Composers], (Istanbul: Pan Yayincilik, 2000)\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Koksal, Pinar}}\n[[Category:1946 births]]\n[[Category:2019 deaths]]\n[[Category:Turkish classical composers]]\n[[Category:People from Adana]]\n[[Category:Female classical composers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name = Ay\u015fe P\u0131nar K\u00f6ksal\n| image = PinarKoksal.jpg\n| image_size = \n| caption = \n| birth_date = 1946\n| birth_place = [[Adana]], Turkey\n| death_date = {{death-date and age|19 August 2019|20 April 1946}}<ref name=sanattanyansimalar />\n| death_place = [[Ankara]], Turkey\n| other_names = \n| known_for =\n| occupation = Composer of Turkish classical music\n| nationality = Turkish\n}}\n'''Ay\u015fe P\u0131nar K\u00f6ksal''' (20 April 1946 \u2013 19 August 2019) was a Turkish composer of Turkish classical music.<ref name=\"sanart\" /> \n'''<big>[https://www.pinarkoksal.com/ www.pinarkoksal.com]</big>'''\nShe lived in [[Ankara]] at the time of her death.<ref name=sanattanyansimalar>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sanattanyansimalar.com/besteci-pinar-koksal-vefat-etti/4664/|title=Besteci P\u0131nar K\u00f6ksal vefat etti|date=20 August 2019|website=sanattanyansimalar.com|language=tr|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref><ref name=sozcu>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sozcu.com.tr/2019/gundem/ayse-pinar-koksal-vefat-etti-5291774/|title=Ay\u015fe P\u0131nar K\u00f6ksal vefat etti|website=www.sozcu.com.tr|language=tr|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref>\n\n== Life ==\nK\u00f6ksal was born in [[Adana]], and because her father was a civil servant her childhood was spent in different parts of [[Anatolia]]. She graduated from [[Kayseri]] High School and later studied [[pharmacy]], receiving her diploma from the Private Higher School of Pharmacy in Istanbul.\n\nShe worked for 13 years as a pharmacist, and she was deputy chair of the board at Pet Holding as well as chair of the board for the K\u00f6ksal Education Foundation. She was also a member of the Democratic Party Governing Board, and chair of the party's Art Committee.\n\nFrom 2001 to 2007 she was a member of the Ministry of Justice Penal Institutions and Detention Houses Monitoring Board, a post from which she resigned in April 2007 for reasons of health.\n\nShe was married to Prof. Dr. G\u00fcntekin K\u00f6ksal and had two daughters, Ay\u015fe and Zeynep, as well as five grandchildren: Kaya, Ege, Melissa, Rauf and Sinan.\n\nShe died on August 19, 2019, due to complications caused by an operation.<ref name=sanattanyansimalar /><ref name=sozcu />\n\n==Musical career==\nHer musical training began in [[Artvin]] at the age of 9 with [[mandolin]] and violin lessons<ref name=akustik /> from Hasan \u00c7\u0131tak (1955\u201357). At the age of 15 she took [[accordion]] lessons in Kayseri (1961\u201362), and at 36 piano lessons from Veli Gerasim. It was at this time that she made her first compositions (1982\u201383). Her very first composition was \"With You I'm Full, Without You an Empty Shell\" (Waltz of Happiness),<ref>{{YouTube|S46HpX5Ks40}}</ref> a work in the Acemk\u00fcrdi makam for which she wrote the words as well as the music. Her first lessons in Turkish Art Music came from the late composer and artist Sadi Ho\u015fses<ref name=sanart /> (1984). After 1996 she studied for an extended period from the tanburist and composer Y\u0131lmaz Pakal\u0131nlar.<ref name=sanart /> K\u00f6ksal played the lute<ref name=sanart /> and has composed some 120 works, of which 74 are in the TRT ([[Turkish Radio and Television Corporation]]) repertory.<ref name=sanart /> A number of her compositions have been arranged polyphonically, while her works are performed throughout Turkey by various choirs, as well as being rendered on radio stations and television channels. In the year 2000 her album \"\u0130\u00e7imdeki Duygular\" was released, comprising works performed by TRT and Ministry of Culture artists.\n\nHers were the first Turkish art music compositions to be performed polyphonically, on December 16, 2003, by the Orfeon Chamber Chorus with soprano Leyla \u00c7olako\u011flu, tenor Hakan Aysev and bass Deva \u00c7olako\u011flu under the direction of conductor Bujor Hoinic. Her works were sung in the musical fantasy ''Cabaret Opera'' staged by the State Opera and Ballet Company and directed by G\u00fcr\u00e7il \u00c7elikta\u015f, and this work became part of the opera repertory (2004\u20132005). Her works have also been performed by symphony orchestras.\n\nHer works are mentioned in three books by the composer [[Turhan Ta\u015fan]], ''Women Composers'' (2000),<ref name=womcom /> ''Pharmacist Artists in Turkish Music'' (2001) and ''Doctor and Pharmacist Artists in Turkish Music'' (2011). In his master's dissertation \"Steps Toward Modernization in Turkish Music During the Republican Era\" (2004) the kanun artist and composer Halil Alt\u0131nk\u00f6pr\u00fc gives composer K\u00f6ksal's works as examples. She has also served on the jury in the Turkish-Style Music Composition Contest held by TRT.<ref name=akustik />   Her compositions also appear in ''The Collected Works of Turkish Art Music Composers'' by Rahmi Kalayc\u0131o\u011flu. In addition, her instrumental works are part of ''Kanun Egzersizleri ve E\u011fitimi'' (Exercises and Training for the Kanun), a book by the kanun artist and composer \u00d6zdemir Haf\u0131zo\u011flu, who is on the faculty of the music department at the K.T.U. Fatih School of Education.\n\nK\u00f6ksal's album ''A\u015fk Senfonisi'' (Symphony of Love), featuring Hakan Aysev and G\u00f6ksel Baktagir, has been released in October 2010.\n\nIn terms of number of works in the TRT repertory she ranks in the top three among the 250 female composers since the 17th century.<ref name=sanart />\n\n==Other interests==\nIn addition to all these endeavors she was interested in psychology as well as all branches of art including cinema, painting, the theater and dance, and she was also a photographer. Her first solo exhibition of photography, \"Do\u011fan\u0131n \u00c7o\u015fkusu\", was held in February 2004,<ref name=akustik /> and her second, \"Do\u011fan\u0131n \u00c7o\u015fkusu II\", in May 2010. Both shows were held in [[Ankara]].\n\n==References==\n<references>\n<ref name=akustik>{{cite web|url=http://www.akustikmuzik.com/sanatcidetay.asp?id=25|title=PINAR K\u00d6KSAL|work=Akustik M\u00fczik|accessdate=2010-10-08}}</ref>\n<ref name=sanart>{{cite web|url=http://www.sanart.org.tr/PDFler/69.pdf|title=Women Composers in Turkish Classical (Allaturca) Music|work=International Congress of Aesthetics 2007 \"Aesthetics Bridging Cultures\"|author=Yasemin L\u00fcmal\u0131|date=2007-10-04|format=pdf|accessdate=2010-10-08}}</ref>\n{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Duygu-Pinari-Spring-Emotions-K\u00f6ksal/dp/B0038WCG4U|title=Duygu Pinari / Spring of Emotions|work=amazon.com|accessdate=2010-10-08}}\n<ref name=womcom>{{cite book|author=Turhan Ta\u015fan|title=Kadin Bestecileri (Women Composers)|publisher=Pan Yayincilik|year=2000|location=Istanbul}}</ref>\n</references>\n\n==Further reading==\n*Turhan Tasan, ''Kadin Bestecileri'' [Women Composers], (Istanbul: Pan Yayincilik, 2000)\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Koksal, Pinar}}\n[[Category:1946 births]]\n[[Category:2019 deaths]]\n[[Category:Turkish classical composers]]\n[[Category:People from Adana]]\n[[Category:Female classical composers]]\n", "name_user": "Eryilmazomer", "label": "safe", "comment": "format web link", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/P%C4%B1nar_K%C3%B6ksal"}
{"title_page": "Mitchell Silk", "text_new": "{{bareurls|date=April 2020}}\n{{short description|Assistant Secretary of the Treasury}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name                      = Mitchell Allen Silk \n| image                     =\n| office                    = Assistant Secretary of the Treasury for International Markets and Development\n| president                 = [[Donald Trump]]\n| term_start                = TBD<br/>Acting: July 2019 \u2013 TBD\n| term_end                  =\n| predecessor               = [[Heath Tarbert]]\n| successor                 = \n| caption                   = \n| birth_name                = Moyshe Silk \n| birth_date                = {{birth date and age|1961|10|15}}\n| birth_place               = [[New York City]]\n| residence                 = [[Borough Park, Brooklyn]], NY\n| nationality               = American\n| education                 = [[University of Maryland School of Law]]<br>[[Beijing University]]<br>[[Georgetown University]]<br>[[National Taiwan Normal University]]<br>[[Middlebury College]]\n| spouse                    = Yocheved\n| children                  = 8\n| website                   = \n| box_width                 = \n}}\n'''Mitchell (Moyshe) Allen Silk''' is a lawyer, author and currently the Assistant Secretary at the [[United States Department of the Treasury]] for International Markets and Development. He is an expert in Chinese law and finance.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eenews.net/stories/1060070457|title=TREASURY DEPARTMENT: Mnuchin poised to disband Environment and Energy office|website=www.eenews.net}}</ref><ref name=\"forward.com\">{{cite web|url=https://forward.com/fast-forward/403966/meet-the-hasidic-jew-who-is-key-to-china-us-trade/|title=Meet The Hasidic Jew Who Is Key To China-U.S. Trade|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=\"mishpacha.com\">{{cite web|url=https://mishpacha.com/along-the-silk-road/ |title=Along the Silk Road|website=www.mishpacha.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chabad.org/news/article_cdo/aid/4040032/jewish/A-US-Treasury-Officials-Moving-Encounter-With-Atlanta-Yeshivah-Students.htm|title=A U.S. Treasury Official\u2019s Moving Encounter With Atlanta Yeshivah Students - A small group makes a big impression in Washington, D.C.|website=www.chabad.org}}</ref> He previously served as Deputy Assistant Secretary from October 2017 to July 2019.\n\nSilk is the first and only [[Hasidic]] Jew to hold a senior U.S. administration position.<ref name=\"forward.com\"/><ref name=\"mishpacha.com\"/>\n\n== Education ==\n\nSilk has a [[Juris Doctor]] degree from the [[University of Maryland School of Law]], Certificate in Advanced Studies in Law from [[Beijing University]], and a Bachelor of Science in Foreign Service from [[Georgetown University]].<ref name=\"linkedin.com\">{{cite web|url=https://www.linkedin.com/in/mitchell-silk-9433169/|website=linkedin.com|title=www.linkedin.com/in/mitchell-silk-9433169/|accessdate=2018-06-28}}</ref>\n\nHe also received education at [[National Taiwan Normal University]] and [[Middlebury College]].<ref name=\"linkedin.com\"/>\n\n== Professional career ==\n\nSilk began his professional career as an associate at [[Hughes Hubbard & Reed]] from 1987 to 1990, as an associate at [[Graham & James]] from 1990 to 1992, as a senior associate at [[Chadbourne & Parke]] from 1992 to 1996, as a consultant and eventually a partner and Head of China Practice at [[Allen & Overy]] from 1998 to October 2017. He spent a decade in their Hong Kong office.<ref name=\"linkedin.com\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=22868650&privcapId=1575300&previousCapId=1575300&previousTitle=Allen+&+Overy+LLP|title=Mitchell Silk: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg|website=www.bloomberg.com}}</ref><ref name=\"uscc\">{{cite web|url=https://www.uscc.gov/sites/default/files/6.30.10Silk.pdf|date=2013-02-13|title=Mitchell Silk |accessdate=2018-06-28}}</ref><ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2004/05/25/business/business-travel-frequent-flier-briefly-a-comrade-while-negotiating-in-china.html|title=BUSINESS TRAVEL: FREQUENT FLIER; Briefly a Comrade While Negotiating in China|first=Mitchell|last=Silk|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.concurrences.com/en/authors/mitchell-silk|title=Mitchell Silk - Concurrences|website=www.concurrences.com}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2017, Silk was appointed [[Deputy Assistant Secretary]], International Affairs at the [[U.S. Department of the Treasury]].<ref name=\"forward.com\"/><ref name=\"linkedin.com\"/><ref name=\"propublica\">{{cite web|url=https://projects.propublica.org/trump-town/staffers/mitchell-allen-silk|title=Mitchell Allen Silk &#124; Trump Town|website=ProPublica|accessdate=2018-07-06}}</ref> He was the head of the Office of Investment, Energy and Infrastructure.<ref>https://www.treasury.gov/FOIA/Documents/DO%203rd%20QTR%20FOIA%20LOGS_Redacted_508%20Compliance.pdf</ref>\n\nIn July 2019, he became the acting Assistant Secretary of the Treasury for International Markets. On September 19, 2019, [[President Trump]] formally nominated Silk to be Assistant Secretary of the Treasury for International Markets and Development.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.whitehouse.gov/presidential-actions/president-donald-j-trump-announces-intent-nominate-appoint-personnel-key-administration-posts-30/ |title=President Donald J. Trump Announces Intent to Nominate Personnel to Key Administration Posts|last=|first=|date=September 10, 2019|website=[[The White House]]|access-date=September 18, 2019 |language=en}}</ref> His nomination is currently pending before the [[United States Senate Committee on Banking, Housing, and Urban Affairs|Senate Committee on Banking, Housing, and Urban Affairs]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://congress.gov/nomination/116th-congress/1103|title=PN1103 \u2014 Mitchell A. Silk \u2014 Department of the Treasury|last=|first=|date=September 19, 2019|website=[[United States Congress]]|access-date=September 23, 2019|language=en}}</ref> A hearing on his nomination before the Senate Committee was held on November 20, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.banking.senate.gov/hearings/11/07/2019/nomination-hearing|title= Nomination Hearing|last=|first=|date=|website=[[United States Senate]]|access-date=November 14, 2019|language=en}}</ref> On April 21, 2020, the [[United States Senate]] confirmed his nomination by [[voice vote]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://boropark24.com/news/boro-park-resident-confirmed-to-top-treasury-position|title=Boro Park Resident Confirmed to Top Treasury Position \u2013 Boro Park 24|website=boropark24.com|access-date=2020-04-22}}</ref> Silk became the first Hasidic Jew to be confirmed to a senior U.S. administration position.<ref>https://www.jns.org/senate-confirms-chassidic-jew-for-first-ever-senior-position-in-us-administration/</ref><ref>https://www.jpost.com/diaspora/first-ever-hassidic-jew-appointed-as-us-assistant-secretary-625450</ref><ref>https://jewishinsider.com/2020/04/mitchell-silk-confirmed-as-treasury-assistant-secretary/</ref><ref>https://www.i24news.tv/en/news/international/americas/1587575751-us-senate-confirms-first-ultra-orthodox-jew-to-senior-government-position</ref>\n\n== Published work ==\n===Books===\nSilk has published a book on Chinese environmental protection law titled: \u201c''China's marine environmental protection law: The dragon creeping in murky waters''\u201d,<ref name=\"amazon\">{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Chinas-marine-environmental-protection-law/dp/0942182731/ref=la_B001KCKYQW_1_1?s=books&ie=UTF8&qid=1530226549&sr=1-1|website=amazon.com|title=China&#39;s marine environmental protection law: The dragon creeping in murky waters (Occasional papers/reprints series in contemporary Asian studies): Mitchell A Silk: 9780942182736: Amazon.com: Books|accessdate=2018-07-06}}</ref> and several other books,\n''Taiwan Trade and Investment Law'',<ref name=\"amazon2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Taiwan-Investment-Maryland-Studies-Politics/dp/0195852893/ref=sr_1_4?s=books&ie=UTF8&qid=1530231679&sr=1-4&dpID=41MODUuO97L&preST=_SY291_BO1,204,203,200_QL40_&dpSrc=srch|website=amazon.com|title=Taiwan Trade and Investment Law (Maryland Studies in East Asian Law and Politics Series ; 12): Mitchell A. Silk: 9780195852899: Amazon.com: Books|accessdate=2018-07-06}}</ref>\n''Environmental Law and Policy in the People's Republic of China''.<ref name=\"amazon3\">{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Environmental-Policy-Peoples-Republic-Hardback/dp/B003F8D6TG/ref=sr_1_3?s=books&ie=UTF8&qid=1530231679&sr=1-3&dpID=41ckJMqrdeL&preST=_SX218_BO1,204,203,200_QL40_&dpSrc=srch|title=Environmental Law and Policy in the People&#39;s Republic of China(Hardback) - 1987 Edition: Mitchell A. Silk Lester Ross : 0884735980963: Amazon.com: Books|website=amazon.com|accessdate=2018-07-06}}</ref>\n\n===Articles===\n''Are Chinese Companies Taking Over the World?'',<ref name=\"uchicago\">{{cite web|url=https://chicagounbound.uchicago.edu/cjil/vol7/iss1/7/|author=Mitchell Silk|website=chicagounbound.uchicago.edu|title=\"Are Chinese Companies Taking Over the World?\" by Mitchell Silk and Richard Malish|accessdate=2018-07-06}}</ref>\n''Taiwan trade and investment law'',<ref name=\"nlb\">{{cite web|url=http://www.nlb.gov.sg/biblio/8839239|title=Taiwan trade and investment law /by Mitchell A. Silk; edited by Mitchell Silk. \u2013 National Library|website=nlb.gov.sg|accessdate=2018-07-06}}</ref>\n''Understanding China\u2019s State Secrets Laws'',<ref name=\"chinabusinessreview\">{{cite web|url=https://www.chinabusinessreview.com/understanding-chinas-state-secrets-laws/|title=Understanding China&#8217;s State Secrets Laws|website=China Business Review|accessdate=2018-07-06}}</ref>\n''Post-Mao China and Environmental Protection: The Effects of Legal and Politico-Economic Reform'',<ref name=\"heinonline\">{{cite web|url=https://heinonline.org/HOL/LandingPage?handle=hein.journals/uclapblj4&div=8&id=&page=|website=heinonline.org|title=Post-Mao China and Environmental Protection: The Effects of Legal and Politico-Economic Reform 4 UCLA Pacific Basin Law Journal 1985|accessdate=2018-07-06}}</ref>\n''New Executive Order Seeks to Jump Start the Effort to Rebuild America\u2019s Infrastructure'',<ref name=\"muckrack\">{{cite web|url=https://muckrack.com/mitchell-silk/articles|title=Articles by Mitchell Silk &#124; Muck Rack|website=Muck Rack|accessdate=2018-07-06}}</ref>\n''G-d Bless the good people Atlanta Georgia'',<ref name=\"chayamushka\">{{cite web|url=http://chayamushka.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/051618-18-19-Features-Silk_Trip-to-the-treasury.pdf|date=2018-05-15|title=G-d Bless GOOD PEOPLE of ATLANTA, GEORGIA |author=MOYSHE (MITCHELL) SILK|accessdate=2018-07-06}}</ref>\n''Natural gas-fired electric power plants: A key element for future U.S. energy policy'',<ref name=\"allenovery\">{{cite web|url=http://www.allenovery.com/SiteCollectionDocuments/Changing_Landscape_of_US_Energy_Market_-_Natural_Gas-Fir.pdf|date=2011-06-22|title=The Changing Landscape of the U.S. Energy Market|author=Mitchell Silk, Paul Mohler, Gary Lazarus and Noah Baer|accessdate=2018-07-06}}</ref>\n''A U.S. Treasury Official\u2019s Moving Encounter With Atlanta Yeshivah Students''.<ref name=\"chabad\">{{cite web|url=https://www.chabad.org/news/article_cdo/aid/4040032/jewish/A-US-Treasury-Officials-Moving-Encounter-With-Atlanta-Yeshivah-Students.htm|title=A U.S. Treasury Official\u2019s Moving Encounter With Atlanta Yeshivah Students - A small group makes a big impression in Washington, D.C. - Chabad-Lubavitch News|website=chabad.org|accessdate=2018-07-06}}</ref>\n\n== Volunteer work ==\nSince 2005 Silk has been doing volunteer work as the Chairman of \u201cAgudath Israel of America Pro Bono Legal Services LLC\u201d at the [[Agudath Israel of America]].<ref name=\"linkedin.com\"/><ref name=\"agudathisrael\">{{cite web|url=https://agudathisrael.org/entrapped-mother-and-children-freed/|title=Entrapped Mother and Children Freed &#124; The Agudah|website=agudathisrael.org|accessdate=2018-07-06}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nTogether with his wife Yocheved, Silk has been a resident of [[Borough Park, Brooklyn]].<ref name=\"mishpacha.com\"/>\n\nHe was sworn in as Deputy Assistant Secretary with an ancient [[Tikkun kor'im]] that had belonged to Rebbe [[Mordechai of Nadvorna]] who was from Silk\u2019s grandfather\u2019s ancestral town.\n\nHe is an expert in Chinese law and finance, speaks four Languages [[Cantonese Chinese]], English, [[Mandarin Chinese]] and [[Yiddish]].<ref name=\"linkedin.com\"/><ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Silk, Mitchell}}\n[[Category:School of Foreign Service alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Baltimore School of Law alumni]]\n[[Category:Peking University alumni]]\n[[Category:National Taiwan Normal University alumni]]\n[[Category:Middlebury College alumni]]\n[[Category:1961 births]]\n[[Category:American lawyers]]\n[[Category:American Orthodox Jews]]\n[[Category:People from Borough Park, Brooklyn]]\n[[Category:United States Department of the Treasury officials]]\n[[Category:Trump administration personnel]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{bareurls|date=April 2020}}\n{{short description|Assistant Secretary of the Treasury}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name                      = Mitchell Allen Silk \n| image                     =\n| office                    = Assistant Secretary of the Treasury for International Markets and Development\n| president                 = [[Donald Trump]]\n| term_start                = TBD<br/>Acting: July 2019 \u2013 TBD\n| term_end                  =\n| predecessor               = [[Heath Tarbert]]\n| successor                 = \n| caption                   = \n| birth_name                = Moyshe Silk \n| birth_date                = {{birth date and age|1961|10|15}}\n| birth_place               = [[New York City]]\n| residence                 = [[Borough Park, Brooklyn]], NY\n| nationality               = American\n| education                 = [[University of Maryland School of Law]]<br>[[Beijing University]]<br>[[Georgetown University]]<br>[[National Taiwan Normal University]]<br>[[Middlebury College]]\n| spouse                    = Yocheved\n| children                  = 8\n| website                   = \n| box_width                 = \n}}\n'''Mitchell (Moyshe) Allen Silk''' is a lawyer, author and currently the Assistant Secretary at the [[United States Department of the Treasury]] for International Markets and Development. He is an expert in Chinese law and finance.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eenews.net/stories/1060070457|title=TREASURY DEPARTMENT: Mnuchin poised to disband Environment and Energy office|website=www.eenews.net}}</ref><ref name=\"forward.com\">{{cite web|url=https://forward.com/fast-forward/403966/meet-the-hasidic-jew-who-is-key-to-china-us-trade/|title=Meet The Hasidic Jew Who Is Key To China-U.S. Trade|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=\"mishpacha.com\">{{cite web|url=https://mishpacha.com/along-the-silk-road/ |title=Along the Silk Road|website=www.mishpacha.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chabad.org/news/article_cdo/aid/4040032/jewish/A-US-Treasury-Officials-Moving-Encounter-With-Atlanta-Yeshivah-Students.htm|title=A U.S. Treasury Official\u2019s Moving Encounter With Atlanta Yeshivah Students - A small group makes a big impression in Washington, D.C.|website=www.chabad.org}}</ref> He previously served as Deputy Assistant Secretary from October 2017 to July 2019.\n\nSilk is the first and only [[Hasidic]] Jew to hold a senior U.S. administration position.<ref name=\"forward.com\"/><ref name=\"mishpacha.com\"/>\n\n== Education ==\n\nSilk has a [[Juris Doctor]] degree from the [[University of Maryland School of Law]], Certificate in Advanced Studies in Law from [[Beijing University]], and a Bachelor of Science in Foreign Service from [[Georgetown University]].<ref name=\"linkedin.com\">{{cite web|url=https://www.linkedin.com/in/mitchell-silk-9433169/|website=linkedin.com|title=www.linkedin.com/in/mitchell-silk-9433169/|accessdate=2018-06-28}}</ref>\n\nHe also received education at [[National Taiwan Normal University]] and [[Middlebury College]].<ref name=\"linkedin.com\"/>\n\n== Professional career ==\n\nSilk began his professional career as an associate at [[Hughes Hubbard & Reed]] from 1987 to 1990, as an associate at [[Graham & James]] from 1990 to 1992, as a senior associate at [[Chadbourne & Parke]] from 1992 to 1996, as a consultant and eventually a partner and Head of China Practice at [[Allen & Overy]] from 1998 \u2013 October 2017. He spent a decade in their Hong Kong office.<ref name=\"linkedin.com\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=22868650&privcapId=1575300&previousCapId=1575300&previousTitle=Allen+&+Overy+LLP|title=Mitchell Silk: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg|website=www.bloomberg.com}}</ref><ref name=\"uscc\">{{cite web|url=https://www.uscc.gov/sites/default/files/6.30.10Silk.pdf|date=2013-02-13|title=Mitchell Silk |accessdate=2018-06-28}}</ref><ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2004/05/25/business/business-travel-frequent-flier-briefly-a-comrade-while-negotiating-in-china.html|title=BUSINESS TRAVEL: FREQUENT FLIER; Briefly a Comrade While Negotiating in China|first=Mitchell|last=Silk|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.concurrences.com/en/authors/mitchell-silk|title=Mitchell Silk - Concurrences|website=www.concurrences.com}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2017, Silk was appointed [[Deputy Assistant Secretary]], International Affairs at the [[U.S. Department of the Treasury]].<ref name=\"forward.com\"/><ref name=\"linkedin.com\"/><ref name=\"propublica\">{{cite web|url=https://projects.propublica.org/trump-town/staffers/mitchell-allen-silk|title=Mitchell Allen Silk &#124; Trump Town|website=ProPublica|accessdate=2018-07-06}}</ref> He was the head of the Office of Investment, Energy and Infrastructure.<ref>https://www.treasury.gov/FOIA/Documents/DO%203rd%20QTR%20FOIA%20LOGS_Redacted_508%20Compliance.pdf</ref>\n\nIn July 2019, he became the acting Assistant Secretary of the Treasury for International Markets. On September 19, 2019, [[President Trump]] formally nominated Silk to be Assistant Secretary of the Treasury for International Markets and Development.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.whitehouse.gov/presidential-actions/president-donald-j-trump-announces-intent-nominate-appoint-personnel-key-administration-posts-30/ |title=President Donald J. Trump Announces Intent to Nominate Personnel to Key Administration Posts|last=|first=|date=September 10, 2019|website=[[The White House]]|access-date=September 18, 2019 |language=en}}</ref> His nomination is currently pending before the [[United States Senate Committee on Banking, Housing, and Urban Affairs|Senate Committee on Banking, Housing, and Urban Affairs]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://congress.gov/nomination/116th-congress/1103|title=PN1103 \u2014 Mitchell A. Silk \u2014 Department of the Treasury|last=|first=|date=September 19, 2019|website=[[United States Congress]]|access-date=September 23, 2019|language=en}}</ref> A hearing on his nomination before the Senate Committee was held on November 20, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.banking.senate.gov/hearings/11/07/2019/nomination-hearing|title= Nomination Hearing|last=|first=|date=|website=[[United States Senate]]|access-date=November 14, 2019|language=en}}</ref> On April 21, 2020, the [[United States Senate]] confirmed his nomination by [[voice vote]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://boropark24.com/news/boro-park-resident-confirmed-to-top-treasury-position|title=Boro Park Resident Confirmed to Top Treasury Position \u2013 Boro Park 24|website=boropark24.com|access-date=2020-04-22}}</ref> Silk became the first Hasidic Jew to be confirmed to a senior U.S. administration position.<ref>https://www.jns.org/senate-confirms-chassidic-jew-for-first-ever-senior-position-in-us-administration/</ref><ref>https://www.jpost.com/diaspora/first-ever-hassidic-jew-appointed-as-us-assistant-secretary-625450</ref><ref>https://jewishinsider.com/2020/04/mitchell-silk-confirmed-as-treasury-assistant-secretary/</ref><ref>https://www.i24news.tv/en/news/international/americas/1587575751-us-senate-confirms-first-ultra-orthodox-jew-to-senior-government-position</ref>\n\n== Published work ==\n===Books===\nSilk has published a book on Chinese environmental protection law titled: \u201c''China's marine environmental protection law: The dragon creeping in murky waters''\u201d,<ref name=\"amazon\">{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Chinas-marine-environmental-protection-law/dp/0942182731/ref=la_B001KCKYQW_1_1?s=books&ie=UTF8&qid=1530226549&sr=1-1|website=amazon.com|title=China&#39;s marine environmental protection law: The dragon creeping in murky waters (Occasional papers/reprints series in contemporary Asian studies): Mitchell A Silk: 9780942182736: Amazon.com: Books|accessdate=2018-07-06}}</ref> and several other books,\n''Taiwan Trade and Investment Law'',<ref name=\"amazon2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Taiwan-Investment-Maryland-Studies-Politics/dp/0195852893/ref=sr_1_4?s=books&ie=UTF8&qid=1530231679&sr=1-4&dpID=41MODUuO97L&preST=_SY291_BO1,204,203,200_QL40_&dpSrc=srch|website=amazon.com|title=Taiwan Trade and Investment Law (Maryland Studies in East Asian Law and Politics Series ; 12): Mitchell A. Silk: 9780195852899: Amazon.com: Books|accessdate=2018-07-06}}</ref>\n''Environmental Law and Policy in the People's Republic of China''.<ref name=\"amazon3\">{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Environmental-Policy-Peoples-Republic-Hardback/dp/B003F8D6TG/ref=sr_1_3?s=books&ie=UTF8&qid=1530231679&sr=1-3&dpID=41ckJMqrdeL&preST=_SX218_BO1,204,203,200_QL40_&dpSrc=srch|title=Environmental Law and Policy in the People&#39;s Republic of China(Hardback) - 1987 Edition: Mitchell A. Silk Lester Ross : 0884735980963: Amazon.com: Books|website=amazon.com|accessdate=2018-07-06}}</ref>\n\n===Articles===\n''Are Chinese Companies Taking Over the World?'',<ref name=\"uchicago\">{{cite web|url=https://chicagounbound.uchicago.edu/cjil/vol7/iss1/7/|author=Mitchell Silk|website=chicagounbound.uchicago.edu|title=\"Are Chinese Companies Taking Over the World?\" by Mitchell Silk and Richard Malish|accessdate=2018-07-06}}</ref>\n''Taiwan trade and investment law'',<ref name=\"nlb\">{{cite web|url=http://www.nlb.gov.sg/biblio/8839239|title=Taiwan trade and investment law /by Mitchell A. Silk; edited by Mitchell Silk. \u2013 National Library|website=nlb.gov.sg|accessdate=2018-07-06}}</ref>\n''Understanding China\u2019s State Secrets Laws'',<ref name=\"chinabusinessreview\">{{cite web|url=https://www.chinabusinessreview.com/understanding-chinas-state-secrets-laws/|title=Understanding China&#8217;s State Secrets Laws|website=China Business Review|accessdate=2018-07-06}}</ref>\n''Post-Mao China and Environmental Protection: The Effects of Legal and Politico-Economic Reform'',<ref name=\"heinonline\">{{cite web|url=https://heinonline.org/HOL/LandingPage?handle=hein.journals/uclapblj4&div=8&id=&page=|website=heinonline.org|title=Post-Mao China and Environmental Protection: The Effects of Legal and Politico-Economic Reform 4 UCLA Pacific Basin Law Journal 1985|accessdate=2018-07-06}}</ref>\n''New Executive Order Seeks to Jump Start the Effort to Rebuild America\u2019s Infrastructure'',<ref name=\"muckrack\">{{cite web|url=https://muckrack.com/mitchell-silk/articles|title=Articles by Mitchell Silk &#124; Muck Rack|website=Muck Rack|accessdate=2018-07-06}}</ref>\n''G-d Bless the good people Atlanta Georgia'',<ref name=\"chayamushka\">{{cite web|url=http://chayamushka.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/051618-18-19-Features-Silk_Trip-to-the-treasury.pdf|date=2018-05-15|title=G-d Bless GOOD PEOPLE of ATLANTA, GEORGIA |author=MOYSHE (MITCHELL) SILK|accessdate=2018-07-06}}</ref>\n''Natural gas-fired electric power plants: A key element for future U.S. energy policy'',<ref name=\"allenovery\">{{cite web|url=http://www.allenovery.com/SiteCollectionDocuments/Changing_Landscape_of_US_Energy_Market_-_Natural_Gas-Fir.pdf|date=2011-06-22|title=The Changing Landscape of the U.S. Energy Market|author=Mitchell Silk, Paul Mohler, Gary Lazarus and Noah Baer|accessdate=2018-07-06}}</ref>\n''A U.S. Treasury Official\u2019s Moving Encounter With Atlanta Yeshivah Students''.<ref name=\"chabad\">{{cite web|url=https://www.chabad.org/news/article_cdo/aid/4040032/jewish/A-US-Treasury-Officials-Moving-Encounter-With-Atlanta-Yeshivah-Students.htm|title=A U.S. Treasury Official\u2019s Moving Encounter With Atlanta Yeshivah Students - A small group makes a big impression in Washington, D.C. - Chabad-Lubavitch News|website=chabad.org|accessdate=2018-07-06}}</ref>\n\n== Volunteer work ==\nSince 2005 Silk has been doing volunteer work as the Chairman of \u201cAgudath Israel of America Pro Bono Legal Services LLC\u201d at the [[Agudath Israel of America]].<ref name=\"linkedin.com\"/><ref name=\"agudathisrael\">{{cite web|url=https://agudathisrael.org/entrapped-mother-and-children-freed/|title=Entrapped Mother and Children Freed &#124; The Agudah|website=agudathisrael.org|accessdate=2018-07-06}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nTogether with his wife Yocheved, Silk has been a resident of [[Borough Park, Brooklyn]].<ref name=\"mishpacha.com\"/>\n\nHe was sworn in as Deputy Assistant Secretary with an ancient [[Tikkun kor'im]] that had belonged to Rebbe [[Mordechai of Nadvorna]] who was from Silk\u2019s grandfather\u2019s ancestral town.\n\nHe is an expert in Chinese law and finance, speaks four Languages [[Cantonese Chinese]], English, [[Mandarin Chinese]] and [[Yiddish]].<ref name=\"linkedin.com\"/><ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Silk, Mitchell}}\n[[Category:School of Foreign Service alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Baltimore Sc